# Initialise functions

def mpl_plot(plot_title, y_axis_label, x_axis_label, df):
    ''' Static matplotlib plot
    '''
    
    from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter


    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

    sns.set_theme(style="darkgrid")
    plt.style.use('fivethirtyeight')

    custom_colors=['#FF5733','#33FF57', '#3399FF', '#FF33CC', '#FFFF33', '#FF3333', '#33FFCC', '#FF9900', '#9966CC',
                '#00CC66', '#996633', '#FF66CC', '#0099CC', '#FF6600', '#00CC99']


    #plt.hist(df[x_field], df['count'])#, marker='o', linestyle='-')
    sns.barplot(x=df.index, y='count', data=df)


    # Set labels and title
    # plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=12)
    # plt.ylabel('Alerts per year', fontsize=12)
    # plt.title('Static - Alerts per year', fontsize=16)

    plt.xlabel(x_axis_label, fontsize=12)
    plt.ylabel(y_axis_label, fontsize=12)
    plt.title(plot_title, fontsize=16)
    plt.legend('')

    formatter = FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: '{:,.0f}'.format(x))
    plt.gca().yaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)

    plt.xticks(df.index, labels=df.index, rotation=45)

    # Add EU Safetygate title and background
    fig.suptitle('Safety Gate: the EU rapid alert system for dangerous non-food products', color='white', zorder=1)
    rect = plt.Rectangle((0, 0.92), 1.0, .081, transform=fig.transFigure, color='#004494', zorder=-1)
    fig.patches.append(rect)

    # Add bottom annotations
    bottom_annotation = 'Source : Safety Gate: the EU rapid alert system for dangerous non-food products\nhttps://ec.europa.eu/safety-gate-alerts/screen/webReport'
    plt.annotate(bottom_annotation, xy=(0.5, -0.31), xycoords='axes fraction',
                fontsize=10, ha='center', va='center', color='grey')
    
    sub_annot = 'Produced by rodders https://rodders99.github.io/'
    
    plt.annotate(sub_annot, xy=(0.5, -0.358), xycoords='axes fraction',
                fontsize=8, ha='center', va='center', color='grey')

    plt.gca().spines['top'].set_color('grey')
    plt.gca().spines['top'].set_linewidth(2)

    plt.gca().spines['right'].set_color('grey')
    plt.gca().spines['right'].set_linewidth(2)

    plt.gca().spines['bottom'].set_color('grey')
    plt.gca().spines['bottom'].set_linewidth(2)

    plt.gca().spines['left'].set_color('grey')
    plt.gca().spines['left'].set_linewidth(2)
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.85)
    # Show the plot

    # image_path = './Safety_Gate_Logo_sml.png'  # Replace with the actual path to your image
    # image = plt.imread(image_path)
    # imagebox = OffsetImage(image, zoom=1)  # Adjust the zoom factor as needed
    # ab = AnnotationBbox(imagebox, (0.152, .963), frameon=False, xycoords='figure fraction', zorder=2)
    # fig.add_artist(ab)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.grid(True)
    # Show the plot
    plt.show()
#mpl_plot('Risk Category', 'count', 'category',  df)

total_count = df['count'].sum()

# Calculate the sum of 'count' for each 'risk_category'
category_totals = df.groupby('risk_category')['count'].sum().reset_index(name='category_total')

# Calculate the percentage of each risk category
category_totals['percentage'] = (category_totals['category_total'] / total_count) * 100


category_totals
